Introduction
ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ

ChaosFix is very simple and friendly fileecho procesor for DOS.
It is compatible with fido mailer T-Mail or with any FrontDoor style
mailer, it is compatible with ProBoard BBS or any FILES.BBS style BBS, and
it is also compatible with ListGen.

If you haven't heard about Fido, echomail, netmail, etc., then you should
delete ChaosFix immediately.

ChaosFix is guaranteed to do nothing excpet occupying small amount of your
disk space and delete all your favourite files by mistake. However, we hope
that you will use it properely, so you could appreciate all the extraordinary
cool features of the program.

If you have heard about FTSC specifications, you should probably delete
ChaosFix as well.... well, in fact, if you don't mind that ChaosFix lefts
date field of netmails blank and doesn't recognize two networks of same
number in diferents zones (i.e. 2:420 and 128:420 - who uses this ???), you
can go on. What is important, is that ChaosFix uses INTL kludge, so netmails
won't be routed to Autralia or Mars, etc.

As it is typical for shareware from xChaos software, ChaosFix requires
only minimal configuration :-) The very few required parameters are supposed
to be written in ordinery text configuration files - use any simple ASCII
editor to edit them. Most of the required information is shared with T-Mail
mailer (passwords and directories).

I call this technology PLUG'N'PAY.

What is 'fileecho' ?
ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ

I suppose that you have experience with using Fidonet compatible software.
So the standart Fido terminology used here won't be explained in details.
Basicaly, if you are connected to fileecho, you will found plenty of
files waiting for you at your uplink (on hold). To each file, you will be
send one more file with extension TIC. TIC files describes where the main
file came from, what is it's destination and why it is here ?

TIC file is simple text file. It can look like this:

