Instalation and setup
ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ

At first, you should delete czech CHAOSFIX.MSG/HLP/TPL and rename all
ENGLISH.* files to CHAOSFIX.* (TPL/HLP/MSG). You can also delete CZ_ASCII.*
files. The HLP/TPL/MSG files can be also easily edited and for example
translated to any other language.

Points can now follow instructions for easy installation in README.!!! file.

ChaosFix consists of only several files. You can put them into separate
directory or use it in your Fido mailer directory. If you use T-Mail, be
careful not to overwrite your existing DIR.FRQ and PASSWORD.LST files.

Generaly, Chaosfix should be always run in its's home directory. However,
it is possible to use more different configuration files in different
directories.

ChaosFix consists of CHAOSFIX.EXE, CHAOSFIX.TPL, CHAOSFIX.MSG, CHAOSFIX.HLP
and *_ID.BAT files. The simplest solution is to put them all in the same
direcotry.

