CHAOSFIX.CTL: SETUP section
ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ

 Address        ... your Fido address (required!)
[AKA ..       ] ... your AKA's, unlimited number
[Sysop        ] ... sysop's (your) name
[Directories  ] ... full path & name of DIR.FRQ file
 Passwords      ... full path & name of PASSWORD.LST
 Netmail        ... your *.MSG netmail directory
 Inbound        ... your inbound directory
[New          ] ... where newfiles will be stored (default is NEWAREAS\)
[Uplink ..    ] ... uplinks are allowed to add new areas and use "Replaces"
                    keyword in TIC files.


CHAOSFIX.CTL: Extended SETUP section
ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ

Keywords in this section are optional (and are very likely to be completely
useless).


[Friend ..    ] ... Friends have "Guest" status in all areas
[NewAreaType  ] ... default is "Echo", values are Echo/Transit/Free/Private
[FreeString ..] ... if new area name contains this string, it will be "Free"
[PrivateString] ... if new area name contains this string, it will be "Private"
[TransitString] ... if new area name contains this string, it will be "Free"
[EchoString ..] ... if new area name contains this string, it will be "Free"
[LogFile      ] ... file to use instead of CHAOSFIX.LOG
[CommentFiles ] ... how to add coments to FILES.BBS. String consisting from
                    characters L (LDesc in TICs), D (Desc in TICs), F
                    (FILE_ID.DIZ file) and N (do not modify FILES.BBS).
                    Default value is "LD" - "try to use LDesc, if it is not
                    available, use Desc". Typical alternative value is "LFDN" -
                    "try to use LDESC, if it is missing, try to use FILE_ID.DIZ,
                    if it is not available, use Desc, if it is still not availble,
                    do not modify FILES.BBS at all".
[CreatePath   ] ... how to creat path for new areas: No - do not create
                    separate directories (default), T-Fix - T-Fix style of
                    directory names, Allfix - Allfix style of names, ChaosFix
                    - best style of directory names.
[UpdateFrq    ] ... Freq listing to be updated when using "CreatePath"


CHAOSFIX.CTL: AREAS section
ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ

Areas section starts after first use of any of Echo/Transit/Free/Private
keyword. It is being modified automaticaly (by ChaosFix.EXE), so it is
useless to use comments in it.

 Echo           ... declaration of controled fileecho area
 Transit        ... declaration of transit (pass-through) area
 Free           ... declaration of public (free,read/write) area
 Private        ... declaration of private fileecho area
[Desc         ] ... description of area - used in %LIST, etc.
[Path         ] ... path to files. There can be more areas placed in one
                    directory. Path can be defined as a ordinary string
                    ("Path X:\YYY\"), as a line number in DIR.FRQ listing
                    file ("Path 10") or - best solution - '*' character and
                    substring of DIR.FRQ ("*GAMES" = "X:\YYY\GAMES\")
[UseAKA       ] ... which AKA should be used to send files
[Exec         ] ... command which will be executed before processing new file
[FilesBBS     ] ... name of FILES.BBS listing (fedault is "FILES.BBS" :-)
[AddComment   ] ... same sytax as "CommentFiles", but valid only for one area.
                    Typical example of usage: "CommentFiles N"
[Guest ..     ] ... node, which is allowed to see and connect "Private" areas
[NoMail ..    ] ... do not send netmails with comments to this node !
[Rw ..        ] ... downlink allowed to send and connected to recieve files
[Ro ..        ] ... downlink connected to recieve files
[Sleeping ..  ] ... "Rw" keyword after "%PASSIVE" command from downlink
[Inactive ..  ] ... "Ro" keyword after "%PASSIVE" command from downlink


Configuration of your own fileecho
ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ

Simply append following lines to CHAOSFIX.CTL:

Echo MY_LITTLE_ECHO
Desc My experimental fileecho
Path Y:\SOME\STRANGE\PATH

That's all. Now, your downlinks can connect it (or you can connect them with
"Ro" keyword) and you can hatch files to fileecho.


Sysop's point of view
ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ

There are are four command line parametrs:

ChaosFix Fix           ... process inbound *.TIC files
ChaosFix Mgr           ... process netmail *.MSG files
ChaosFix Event         ... process inbound + netmail (1.Mgr 2.Fix)
ChaosFix Hatch [file]  ... send file to fileecho (interactive)

Log file CHAOSFIX.LOG is going to be created in current directory

You will be announced about important changes (like auto adding new area, etc.)
by netmail.

When sending file to fileecho ("Hatch"), the area must be already defined
in ChaosFix.Ctl.

There are several questions to be answered when sending the file to fileecho:

Filename    ... errr, very complicated, isn't it ?
Area        ... short name of area (not it's description - i.e. "GAMES", not
                "S0me c00l gamez"
Description ... _short_ description of the file (not of the area).
Replaces    ... optional - shouldn't be used very much. Simply press <Enter>.

Use FILE_ID.DIZ as...? ... Press 'Y' and HATCH_ID.BAT will be called to
                           extract and/or edit FILE_ID.DIZ. It will be used
                           as long description.

Send file ... now ?  ....  In most cases, you will press 'Y'.

Move file to ... ?  ...... If the file isn't in it's destination directory yet

Replaces more than one ... Important warning - will apear only when "Replaces"
                           was used incorrectly

Update FILES.BBS ? ....... Should the LDesc or Desc be added to FILES.BBS file
                           in the area ?


Downlink's point of view
ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ

Address all requests to 'ChaosFix', 'FileMgr' or 'AllFix' (without quotes).
Your Allfix password (same as session password) goes on the subject line.

In the body of the message to Allfix:

[+]<areaname>         Connect an area
-<areaname>           Disconnect an area
*<areaname>           Temporary disconnect an area
[%]+ALL               Connect all available areas
[%]-ALL               Disconnect all areas
%HELP                 Request this message
%LIST                 Request a list of areas available to you
%QUERY                Request a list of areas to which you are connected
%ACTIVE               Reconnect all temporary disconnected areas
%PASSIVE              Temporary disconnect all connected areas
%MAIL+<oblast>|ALL    Comment files in netmail (in one or all areas)
%MAIL-<oblast>|ALL    Disable file comments


Specifikace
ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ

Hardware: PC XT compatible (for example DOS virtual machines, etc.)

Software: DOS 6.x (uses MOVE, and EDIT commands), T-MAil/ProBoard recomended

Maximum length of text files: 32 kB

Maximum length of variable listings: limitide by ammount of free memory

Maximum number of precessed TICs: depends on your file system

Maximum number of fileeecho areas: cca 100, depends on number of downlinks

Compatibility: FTN/FTSC-001 *.MSG,T-MAIL style DIR.FRQ a PASSWORD.LST,
               ProBoard FILES.BBS,Allfix/Krucifix/T-Fix *.TIC


